\begin_layout Enumerate
The request for an evaluation of the SI method is clearly reasonable.
 However, the examiner confuses the Marko et.
 al.
 study, which used the two loop approximation, with the results Hartree-Fock
 approximation (indeed there is no problem for the SI-2PIEA in the Hartree-Fock
 approximation) which are directly comparable to the SI-3PI results presented
 in chapter 4.
 The Marko et.
 al.
 study is indeed disturbing regarding the validity of the symmetry improvement
 method, at least with a cutoff regulator.
 This is due to the appearance of IR divergences at the two loop level.
 To make any statements about the existence (or otherwise) of SI-3PI solutions
 requires solutions in truncations which can in principle produce IR divergences
, i.e.
 the two or three loop truncations, which remain to be solved.
 Therefore the existence criteria for SI-3PI solutions remains a totally
 open problem.
 A discussion along these lines has been added as the final paragraph of
 section 7.2.
\end_layout

